<H2> 

Kaoru Sumi, Dr. Eng.
<P>
<IMG SRC="kaoru.gif" ALT="my portrait">
</H2>

<P>
Kaoru Sumi is CRL Fellow of
<A HREF="http://www-karc.crl.go.jp/synsophy/index.html">
        Breakthrough21 Nishida Project 
</A>
<BR>
in
<A HREF="http://www-karc.crl.go.jp">
Kansai Advanced Research Center,
</A>
Communications Research Laboratory <BR>
Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications

<P>
Her research interest covers 
Knowledge Engineering,
Communication Support Systems, 
User Modeling, and
Human Interface.
<P>

She is a member of 
Japan Association for Artificial Intelligence (JSAI),
Information Processing Society of Japan (IPSJ), and
Association for Computing Machinery (ACM).

<H2>
<IMG SRC="c1.gif"> 
Education and Career</H2>
Doctor of Engineering at the University of Tokyo
<BR>
(<A HREF="http://www.ai.rcast.u-tokyo.ac.jp/index.html">Hori Laboratory</A> in <A HREF="http://www.rcast.u-tokyo.ac.jp/index.html">Research Center for Advanced Science and Technology</A>)
<BR>
in the 1998 fiscal year.
<P>
Since Oct 1996: Intern Researcher at <A HREF="http://www.mic.atr.co.jp/organization/dept2/index.e.html">Dept.2</A> in <A HREF="http://www.mic.atr.co.jp/index.e.html">ATR MI&C Research Labs,</A><BR>
Since Oct 1998: Researcher at
<A HREF="http://www-karc.crl.go.jp/synsophy/index.html">
        Breakthrough21 Nishida Project 
</A>.

<P>

